 EVALUATION PROCEDURE                                             9137 1451
                                                                  9137 1451
 Adopted procedure is based on careful theoretical                9137 1451
 analysis utilizing available experimental data and               9137 1451
 nuclear reaction model calculations.                             9137 1451
                                                                  9137 1451
 Available experimental data were interpreted  using              9137 1451
 nuclear reaction model code EMPIRE-2.19b33 by                    9137 1451
 M. Herman et al [He01, He02]. This code integrates               9137 1451
 into a single system a number of important modules               9137 1451
 and features, relevant for this evaluation:                      9137 1451
 - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including                 9137 1451
   coupled-channels (ECIS03 by J. Raynal)                         9137 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including                    9137 1451
   HRTW width fluctuation correction                              9137 1451
 - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster                      9137 1451
   emission and Kalbach systematic angular distr.                 9137 1451
   (code PCROSS by R.Capote et al)                                9137 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of                   9137 1451
   each particle, including realistic treatment of                9137 1451
   discrete transitions                                           9137 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL-2 library [Ri03]              9137 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses,                9137 1451
   level density, discrete levels, fission barriers               9137 1451
   and gamma strength functions  based on the RIPL-2              9137 1451
   library [Ri03]                                                 9137 1451
 - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the              9137 1451
   EXFOR/CSISRS library                                           9137 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A. Trkov)                    9137 1451
   coupled to graphical presentation capabilities                 9137 1451
   (code ZVView by V. Zerkin) through the chain of                9137 1451
   PrePro codes by R. Cullen                                      9137 1451
 - Checking codes (CHECKR, FIZCON, PSYCHE)                        9137 1451
 - Support for NJOY                                               9137 1451
